Mission Statement
The mission of North Shore School District 112, a community partnership committed to a world-class education, is to nurture every child to become an inspired learner, a well-rounded individual and contributing member of a global community by striving for excellence within an environment that fosters innovation, respect, engagement and intellectual inquiry.
General Description:
The Database Manager works closely with the Technology Department staff and District staff to provide accurate and reliable District 112 data. Database design, modification and utilization, in keeping with overall district needs, are key responsibilities of the position.
Desired Qualities:
Proficiency in typing and word processing. Data systems order entry a plus. Highly organized and capable of efficiently tracking multiple priorities. Basic computer knowledge. Additional technological knowledge preferred.

Responsibilities:
Maintains student information system (currently Infinite Campus), including beginning and end of year functions, accuracy of data, support for school personnel, training, troubleshooting;
Creates and maintains required reports and is knowledgeable of IWAS/ISBE systems;
Downloads and provides summary analyses of data;
Provides database-programming support of applications through development and Maintenance of application software;
Develops and maintains database documentation;
Develops processes and actively performs database tuning processes and procedures;
Makes technical recommendations regarding division-wide data access and database connectivity;
Maintains custom programs and the databases that they interface with;
Trouble shoots and correct program errors and complete work orders as needed;
Assists with software support for business office, data processing computers, and school wide scanners;
Conducts individual or small group training of staff personnel;
Interacts with multiple databases, systems and functions;
Performs analyses of costs and return on investment of data services across departments;
Assists in the development, scheduling and execution of division wide staff development;
Maintains and develops professional skills through ongoing training and career development, including self-study, classroom training, and industry seminars and workshops;
Interfaces with special education to file reports;
Performs other duties as assigned.

Alternatives to the above qualifications as the Board of Education may find appropriate.

Working Conditions:
Per NSSSA salary schedule, 8 hour work day-12 month position plus excellent benefits, IMRF Retirement Pension, paid sick, personal, bereavement leave and other benefits.

Application Procedure:
Apply on line by completing the on line application and uploading support materials. PLEASE NO CALLS OR EMAILS.

Selection Procedure:
The Chief Technology Officer and Student Information Manager will review on line applications and supporting materials and will call individuals in for interviews. After initial interviews, candidates meet with the Deputy Superintendent who may recommend the individual for hire by the Board of Education.
The North Shore School District is an Equal Opportunity Employer

